A good reporter should ask away.

00:16:08.620 --> 00:16:13.160
Um, well, what were you doing sleeping behind the door?

00:16:13.160 --> 00:16:15.160
If I teach you nothing else in this internship,

00:16:15.160 --> 00:16:17.160
I will teach you to sleep standing up.

00:16:17.160 --> 00:16:19.160
Best skill any journalist can have.

00:16:19.160 --> 00:16:22.160
And anybody who tells you different is a hack.

00:16:22.160 --> 00:16:24.160
No kidding.

00:16:24.160 --> 00:16:26.160
Actually, I am kidding.

00:16:26.160 --> 00:16:28.160
Whoa!

00:16:28.160 --> 00:16:30.160
It's the alarm clock.

00:16:30.160 --> 00:16:32.160
I usually wake myself,

00:16:32.160 --> 00:16:35.160
but a good newsman never takes chances.

00:16:35.160 --> 00:16:38.160
Well, don't you want to turn the alarm off?

00:16:38.160 --> 00:16:40.160
Yes, right. Good.

00:16:40.160 --> 00:16:59.290
You're my intern. Help me find it.

00:16:59.290 --> 00:17:01.290
Okay.

00:17:01.290 --> 00:17:03.290
We've got some work to do.

00:17:03.290 --> 00:17:13.280
Great.

00:17:13.280 --> 00:17:15.280
Say, listen, uh,

00:17:15.280 --> 00:17:17.280
you may be way ahead of me on this,

00:17:17.280 --> 00:17:19.280
but I've got this idea.

00:17:19.280 --> 00:17:22.280
Have you ever thought of using your computer?

00:17:22.280 --> 00:17:27.280
That crazy contraption the newspaper gave to me

00:17:27.280 --> 00:17:29.280
makes me nervous just to look at it.

00:17:29.280 --> 00:17:32.280
But don't you think it could help you get, you know,

00:17:32.280 --> 00:17:34.280
organized?

00:17:34.280 --> 00:17:36.280
Getting organized.

00:17:36.280 --> 00:17:38.280
Great idea, Clarissa.

00:17:38.280 --> 00:17:40.280
That can be your job.

00:17:40.280 --> 00:17:43.280
I want you to take all the stuff that I do

00:17:43.280 --> 00:17:45.280
and organize it.

00:17:45.280 --> 00:17:59.340
I've got it.

00:17:59.340 --> 00:18:01.340
Organize this mess?

00:18:01.340 --> 00:18:05.340
Something tells me I may have bitten off more than I can chew.

00:18:10.340 --> 00:18:13.880
More Clarissa.

00:18:13.880 --> 00:18:16.880
More Snick. After this.

00:18:16.880 --> 00:18:19.880
The ultimate Nickelodeon guts challenge.

00:18:19.880 --> 00:18:22.880
The radical rock, the aggro crag.

00:18:22.880 --> 00:18:25.880
Now, bigger, meaner, and more mountainous than ever.

00:18:25.880 --> 00:18:27.880
Watch Nick put kids on the crag.

00:18:27.880 --> 00:18:30.880
Every weekday at 5.30, 4.30 central, only on Nick.

00:18:30.880 --> 00:18:36.440
Kids, we just want to have fun.

00:18:36.440 --> 00:18:39.440
The kids love kids to a big case number one.

00:18:39.440 --> 00:18:41.440
The Burger King kids fun.

00:18:41.440 --> 00:18:44.440
They're cool to be a kid.

00:18:44.440 --> 00:18:48.440
Now at Burger King, you'll make a starling discovery.

00:18:48.440 --> 00:18:50.440
Introducing dinocrawlers.

00:18:50.440 --> 00:18:53.440
Dinosaurs that crawl were just about anything.

00:18:53.440 --> 00:18:55.440
You can collect all five, one with every kid's meal.

00:18:55.440 --> 00:18:59.440
Only at Burger King, more than dinocrawlers are coming your way.

00:18:59.440 --> 00:19:02.440
The Burger King kids club. I love this place.

00:19:02.440 --> 00:19:06.440
Teen by success, the turtles lost their savage edge.

00:19:06.440 --> 00:19:08.440
Greed is dead.

00:19:08.440 --> 00:19:11.440
It's a new breed carved from the streets.

00:19:11.440 --> 00:19:14.440
Concrete fist, batter, alien flesh.

00:19:14.440 --> 00:19:18.440
One on one as power joins forces with rage.

00:19:18.440 --> 00:19:21.440
Ripping through fear, and no one sheds a tear

00:19:21.440 --> 00:19:23.440
for mutilated mutants.

00:19:23.440 --> 00:19:26.440
Giant warriors crushed by three-cup turtles

00:19:26.440 --> 00:19:30.440
who have shed soft shells for a high dose of reality.

00:19:30.440 --> 00:19:32.440
Economic tournament fighters.

00:19:32.440 --> 00:20:09.240
If a hurricane threatened us, we'd protect our families.

00:20:09.240 --> 00:20:12.240
While a storm of murder and violence is hitting our city,

00:20:12.240 --> 00:20:14.240
and it's time for action.

00:20:14.240 --> 00:20:18.240
One, I'll fight for a walk that any criminal

00:20:18.240 --> 00:20:22.240
convicted of free violent crime goes to jail for life.

00:20:22.240 --> 00:20:25.240
No parole, free strikes, you're out.

00:20:25.240 --> 00:20:29.240
Two, I'll take cops out from behind the desk

00:20:29.240 --> 00:20:31.240
and put them on the street.

00:20:31.240 --> 00:20:34.240
I'll be a mayor fighting on your side.

00:20:34.240 --> 00:20:39.310
Shoulder mounted.

00:20:39.310 --> 00:20:43.660
It weighs just four pounds.

00:20:43.660 --> 00:20:48.660
But it's the most powerful weapon this individual learns to use.

00:20:48.660 --> 00:20:58.930
Because this weapon is the mind of a Marine.

00:20:58.930 --> 00:21:04.370
From the great state of Louisiana, I'm Marine Corporal Clark.

00:21:04.370 --> 00:21:07.370
Maybe you can be one of us.

00:21:07.370 --> 00:21:21.260
Okay, remember the real world?

00:21:21.260 --> 00:21:23.260
Well, it's pretty unreal.

00:21:23.260 --> 00:21:25.260
How have things been going so far?

00:21:25.260 --> 00:21:28.260
Let's turn to a fast-breaking intern update.

00:21:28.260 --> 00:21:30.260
After Arnie decided he was too disorganized

00:21:30.260 --> 00:21:32.260
for us to start getting organized,

00:21:32.260 --> 00:21:35.260
he initiated me into the world of sports.

00:21:35.260 --> 00:21:37.260
Intern Hour One.

00:21:37.260 --> 00:21:39.260
We watched a Brazilian soccer-playoff game.

00:21:39.260 --> 00:21:41.260
I took notes.

00:21:41.260 --> 00:21:44.180
Yes!

00:21:44.180 --> 00:21:47.180
But Arnie's the one who really got a kick out of it.

00:21:47.180 --> 00:21:49.180
Intern Hour Two.

00:21:49.180 --> 00:21:51.180
Arnie teaches me why it's important for a journalist

00:21:51.180 --> 00:21:53.180
to know a foreign language.

00:21:53.180 --> 00:21:56.180
Mugugai Pan, Mushulo Mane,

00:21:56.180 --> 00:21:59.180
Subgum Town,

00:21:59.180 --> 00:22:01.180
Darn!

00:22:01.180 --> 00:22:03.180
Did you want some duck sauce?

00:22:03.180 --> 00:22:06.180
I guess it's hard to write on an empty stomach.

00:22:07.180 --> 00:22:10.180
And finally, Intern Hour Three.

00:22:10.180 --> 00:22:13.180
Arnie had me watch highlights of the 86 World Series.

00:22:13.180 --> 00:22:15.180
The Mets versus the Red Sox.

00:22:15.180 --> 00:22:17.180
Watch this call. Watch this call.

00:22:17.180 --> 00:22:20.180
You bump! You bump!

00:22:20.180 --> 00:22:23.180
God, I love baseball.

00:22:23.180 --> 00:22:27.180
You should have seen him cry when the Mets won again.

00:22:27.180 --> 00:22:29.180
Meanwhile, I've been filing everything

00:22:29.180 --> 00:22:31.180
from NCAA basketball stats

00:22:31.180 --> 00:22:33.180
to Olympic ping pong regulations.

00:22:33.180 --> 00:22:36.180
I'm going to get Arnie organized or else.

00:22:36.180 --> 00:22:44.550
I just hope my dad hasn't been too hard on Sam.

00:22:44.550 --> 00:22:46.550
Good, Sam. Good.

00:22:46.550 --> 00:22:48.550
Now, take the T-square,

00:22:48.550 --> 00:22:51.550
firmly butt lightly in your left hand.

00:22:51.550 --> 00:22:53.550
Now, trace along the edge

00:22:53.550 --> 00:22:56.550
with an authoritative yet loving stroke.

00:22:56.550 --> 00:22:59.550
It's thrilling, isn't it?

00:22:59.550 --> 00:23:01.550
I guess so.

00:23:01.550 --> 00:23:04.550
What?

00:23:04.550 --> 00:23:07.550
Well, you went too far. See, you went over the line.

00:23:07.550 --> 00:23:09.550
Oh, sorry, Mr. Darling.

00:23:09.550 --> 00:23:11.550
Ah, sorry, Sam. It's all right.

00:23:11.550 --> 00:23:15.790
It's your first day. You're bound to make mistakes.

00:23:15.790 --> 00:23:17.790
Hey, how's it going?

00:23:17.790 --> 00:23:19.790
Great.

00:23:19.790 --> 00:23:21.790
You guys almost done?

00:23:21.790 --> 00:23:23.790
Yep, all done.

00:23:23.790 --> 00:23:25.790
Sam, one second.

00:23:25.790 --> 00:23:28.790
Remember, putting our tools away is half the job.

00:23:28.790 --> 00:23:31.790
Oh, right, Mr. Darling. I forgot.

00:23:31.790 --> 00:23:33.790
Now, everything here has been marked

00:23:33.790 --> 00:23:35.790
for its specific container.

00:23:35.790 --> 00:23:37.790
Let's see.

00:23:37.790 --> 00:23:40.790
It's always good to have your things organized.

00:23:40.790 --> 00:23:46.340
Sure is, Mr. Darling.

00:23:46.340 --> 00:23:48.340
Now, what are you doing out of your box?

00:23:48.340 --> 00:23:50.340
Dad?

00:23:50.340 --> 00:23:52.340
What would you say about an advance in my allowance?

00:23:52.340 --> 00:23:56.340
Ferguson, I am not giving you $75 for some fancy haircut.

00:23:56.340 --> 00:23:58.340
I only need five more dollars.

00:23:58.340 --> 00:24:00.340
I cashed in the war bond that Aunt Dornie

00:24:00.340 --> 00:24:02.340
gave me for my 10th birthday.

00:24:02.340 --> 00:24:04.340
Oh, all right.

00:24:04.340 --> 00:24:06.340
But I still say that there's nothing wrong

00:24:06.340 --> 00:24:08.340
with staying on the barber.

00:24:08.340 --> 00:24:10.340
Thanks.

00:24:10.340 --> 00:24:13.340
Take one long last look at the old me,

00:24:13.340 --> 00:24:15.340
because when I return for Monsieur Pierre's,

00:24:15.340 --> 00:24:18.340
I will be the new me.

00:24:18.340 --> 00:24:21.340
That's a lot to ask from a haircut.

00:24:21.340 --> 00:24:23.340
Well, Sam, it was a good first day.

00:24:23.340 --> 00:24:25.340
I'll see you tomorrow at 3 p.m.

00:24:25.340 --> 00:24:30.320
Sharp? Sharp.

00:24:30.320 --> 00:24:34.320
That's my dad. He's nothing if he's not punctual.

00:24:34.320 --> 00:24:37.320
Yeah, so how'd it go with my dad?

00:24:37.320 --> 00:24:40.320
Good. Fine. Really good.

00:24:40.320 --> 00:24:43.320
Fine. What about you?

00:24:43.320 --> 00:24:47.320
Great. I learned a whole bunch of stuff from your dad.

00:24:47.320 --> 00:24:49.320
I mean, I never realized that refilling the lead

00:24:49.320 --> 00:24:52.320
in a mechanical pencil was such an exact science.

00:24:52.320 --> 00:24:54.320
Yeah, I should have warned you.

00:24:54.320 --> 00:24:56.320
My dad can be a real stickler for details.

00:24:56.320 --> 00:24:58.320
Hey, but in a good way.

00:24:58.320 --> 00:25:00.320
Yeah, in a good way.

00:25:00.320 --> 00:25:04.320
Well, um, I better get home and reheat the chow mein.

00:25:04.320 --> 00:25:06.320
Yeah.

00:25:06.320 --> 00:25:08.320
Aunt Dornie really enjoys his Chinese food.

00:25:08.320 --> 00:25:10.320
See you tomorrow.

00:25:10.320 --> 00:25:14.430
See you. Oh, well, I've signed up.

00:25:14.430 --> 00:25:17.430
I'm in the intern business and I'm sticking with it.

00:25:17.430 --> 00:25:19.430
What's the worst that can happen?

00:25:19.430 --> 00:25:21.430
I can handle Sam's dad.

00:25:21.430 --> 00:25:23.430
Sam can handle my dad.

00:25:23.430 --> 00:25:25.430
And Sam and I are just going to have to handle each other

00:25:25.430 --> 00:25:49.580
with kid gloves till this whole thing is over.

00:25:49.580 --> 00:25:51.580
Clarissa! Ready to get cracking?

00:25:51.580 --> 00:25:54.580
Great, but, um, do you ever work at the dispatch?

00:25:54.580 --> 00:25:56.580
You know, I wouldn't mind going down there.

00:25:56.580 --> 00:25:58.580
I know, but I've got this hang up.

00:25:58.580 --> 00:26:00.580
I can't seem to write in a place where I'm supposed to be writing.

00:26:00.580 --> 00:26:02.580
Oh, I get it.

00:26:02.580 --> 00:26:07.580
Setting your own environment can be very important for a journalist.

00:26:07.580 --> 00:26:10.580
Now, Sam tells me you're a good editor.

00:26:10.580 --> 00:26:13.580
Here's your chance.

00:26:13.580 --> 00:26:16.580
This is next week's column.

00:26:16.580 --> 00:26:20.580
I need you to cut it in half with this.

00:26:20.580 --> 00:26:22.580
Be ruthless.

00:26:22.580 --> 00:26:24.580
But this column's about boxing.

00:26:24.580 --> 00:26:27.580
I don't know anything about boxing.

00:26:27.580 --> 00:26:30.580
Is everything you need to know about the sweet science?

00:26:30.580 --> 00:26:33.580
Give it a shot and we'll compare the notes.

00:26:33.580 --> 00:26:35.580
And hey, why don't you go home and work on that?

00:26:35.580 --> 00:26:38.580
Home? Oh, don't you ever go to the newsroom?

00:26:38.580 --> 00:26:40.580
Hey, no way.

00:26:40.580 --> 00:26:42.580
Why do you think I chose sports?

00:26:42.580 --> 00:26:44.580
See you tomorrow, Clarissa. Ciao.

00:26:44.580 --> 00:26:46.580
Okay, ciao.

00:26:46.580 --> 00:26:56.760
Well, this isn't exactly how I pictured the real world of journalism.

00:26:56.760 --> 00:26:58.760
But at least I've got a real assignment.

00:26:58.760 --> 00:27:03.890
Hi, Sam.

00:27:03.890 --> 00:27:09.090
Hey, Clarissa.

00:27:09.090 --> 00:27:12.090
I just came by to set up a time with your dad for tomorrow's interning session.

00:27:12.090 --> 00:27:14.090
Aren't you getting a little ahead of yourself?

00:27:14.090 --> 00:27:16.090
Not even close.

00:27:16.090 --> 00:27:18.090
Mr. Darling, I mean your dad,

00:27:18.090 --> 00:27:20.090
well, he likes things just a certain way.

00:27:20.090 --> 00:27:22.090
Way in advance.

00:27:22.090 --> 00:27:25.090
Yeah, some people have really weird working habits.

00:27:25.090 --> 00:27:27.090
What does that mean?

00:27:27.090 --> 00:27:28.090
Oh, nothing.

00:27:28.090 --> 00:27:30.090
I just think it's strange that your daddy's Chinese

00:27:30.090 --> 00:27:32.090
take out every single day of his life

00:27:32.090 --> 00:27:34.090
and writes all his notes on the napkins.

00:27:34.090 --> 00:27:37.090
What's so weird about that? It's his personal style.

00:27:37.090 --> 00:27:40.090
Well, hasn't he ever heard that too much MSG can make you crazy?

00:27:40.090 --> 00:27:43.090
Well, there's crazy, and then there's crazy.

00:27:43.090 --> 00:27:45.090
What does that mean?

00:27:45.090 --> 00:27:47.090
Oh, nothing. Just that I call having a proper name

00:27:47.090 --> 00:27:49.090
for every single one of your pencils.

00:27:49.090 --> 00:27:51.090
A little on the weird side.

00:27:51.090 --> 00:27:53.090
Are you talking about my dad?

00:27:53.090 --> 00:27:55.090
Oh, does your dad do that?

00:27:55.090 --> 00:27:57.090
Well, at least he sleeps in a bed.

00:27:57.090 --> 00:27:59.090
Does your dad sleep?

00:27:59.090 --> 00:28:01.090
I was beginning to think he stayed up all night

00:28:01.090 --> 00:28:03.090
rearranging his paper clips.

00:28:03.090 --> 00:28:05.090
I was afraid this was gonna happen.

00:28:05.090 --> 00:28:07.090
My dad drives you crazy, but it's worse

00:28:07.090 --> 00:28:09.090
when he drives your friends crazy.

00:28:09.090 --> 00:28:11.090
Yeah, actually, it's kind of embarrassing.

00:28:11.090 --> 00:28:13.090
I've given up cleaning up after him.

00:28:13.090 --> 00:28:15.090
You know what the worst thing is?

00:28:15.090 --> 00:28:16.090
What?

00:28:16.090 --> 00:28:19.090
On top of everything else, I feel like I'm not a good intern.

00:28:19.090 --> 00:28:21.090
I feel like your dad thinks I'm a dweeb.

00:28:21.090 --> 00:28:23.090
No, he thinks you're great. He told me last night.

00:28:23.090 --> 00:28:25.090
If anyone's a dweeb, it's me.

00:28:25.090 --> 00:28:27.090
I can't even stack the erasers right.

00:28:27.090 --> 00:28:30.090
Sam, my dad loves you. He just gets carried away.

00:28:30.090 --> 00:28:32.090
Yeah, stuff is really cool.

00:28:32.090 --> 00:28:35.090
I guess details are pretty essential for an architect.

00:28:35.090 --> 00:28:37.090
And your dad's article is great.

00:28:37.090 --> 00:28:39.090
He does have some pretty unusual working habits,

00:28:39.090 --> 00:28:41.090
but I guess they work for him.

00:28:41.090 --> 00:28:43.090
Maybe we should just go with the flow.

00:28:43.090 --> 00:28:44.090
Yeah.

00:28:44.090 --> 00:28:47.090
Let's stop asking what our internships can do for us

00:28:47.090 --> 00:28:50.090
and start asking what we can do for our internships.

00:28:50.090 --> 00:28:56.600
Uh-huh.

00:28:56.600 --> 00:28:59.600
Very nice cut. Very nice.

00:28:59.600 --> 00:29:02.810
Marissa.

00:29:02.810 --> 00:29:03.810
Yeah?

00:29:03.810 --> 00:29:05.810
Don't read over my shoulder. It makes me nervous.

00:29:05.810 --> 00:29:07.810
Oh, sorry. Sorry.

00:29:08.810 --> 00:29:12.660
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

00:29:12.660 --> 00:29:14.660
Well, it's time then.

00:29:14.660 --> 00:29:16.660
Time for what?

00:29:16.660 --> 00:29:18.660
Remember that game I made you watch the other day?

00:29:18.660 --> 00:29:20.660
The Brazilian soccer match?

00:29:20.660 --> 00:29:23.660
This batch needs a two-paragraph blurb on it by tomorrow.

00:29:23.660 --> 00:29:25.660
Go. Write it down.

00:29:25.660 --> 00:29:28.660
Me? By myself? Really?

00:29:28.660 --> 00:29:30.660
Here's a napkin.

00:29:30.660 --> 00:29:32.660
And a pen.

00:29:32.660 --> 00:29:34.660
Go to it.

00:29:34.660 --> 00:29:36.660
Just start writing?

00:29:36.660 --> 00:29:40.450
Sure.

00:29:40.450 --> 00:29:43.450
You always say a writer's environment is important, right?

00:29:43.450 --> 00:29:44.450
You bet.

00:29:44.450 --> 00:29:48.450
Well, my ideal journalistic environment would be a little bit more...

00:29:48.450 --> 00:29:50.450
well, computerized.

00:29:50.450 --> 00:29:53.450
Do you mind if I use that?

00:29:53.450 --> 00:29:58.000
Uh-huh.

00:29:58.000 --> 00:30:00.000
Okay. Ready to go.

00:30:00.000 --> 00:30:02.000
See, this way, instead of using napkins,

00:30:02.000 --> 00:30:05.000
you can just open a file for each different thought.

00:30:05.000 --> 00:30:07.000
What you're saying is,

00:30:07.000 --> 00:30:10.000
I can use my computer for something besides a coaster.

00:30:10.000 --> 00:30:12.000
Only if it works for you.

00:30:12.000 --> 00:30:15.000
Hey, Arnie, would you mind not looking over my shoulder?

00:30:15.000 --> 00:30:17.000
It tends to make a writer nervous.

00:30:17.000 --> 00:30:19.000
Oh, where'd you learn that?

00:30:19.000 --> 00:30:22.000
Oh, just something I picked up around the newsroom.

00:30:22.000 --> 00:30:28.650
Chicken chow mein, egg rolls, lychee nuts.

00:30:28.650 --> 00:30:31.650
I think I've got an acceptable number of food groups represented.

00:30:31.650 --> 00:30:34.650
Your Chinese takeout consumption has gone a little out of control

00:30:34.650 --> 00:30:36.650
since you finished your internship, Clarison.

00:30:36.650 --> 00:30:38.650
After-school snack of champions.

00:30:38.650 --> 00:30:40.650
How are you doing, Sam?

00:30:40.650 --> 00:30:42.650
That sounds so familiar.

00:30:42.650 --> 00:30:44.650
Butchery. Yeah, butchery.

00:30:44.650 --> 00:30:46.650
That's what I'd call it.

00:30:46.650 --> 00:30:48.650
Using any other word would be candy-coating the situation.

00:30:48.650 --> 00:30:50.650
Ferguson, it's not really that bad.

00:30:50.650 --> 00:30:53.650
Well, not for a Parisian lapdog.

00:30:53.650 --> 00:30:56.650
Well, I'm sure Monsieur LeStain can fix it.

00:30:56.650 --> 00:30:59.650
Okay, but no lollipops.

00:30:59.650 --> 00:31:01.650
Is that today's paper?

00:31:01.650 --> 00:31:07.860
